45
00:09:45,592 --> 00:09:47,970
- Thank God.
- What are you doing up there?

46
00:09:48,053 --> 00:09:52,433
<i>There's been
an elevator malfunction, so just relax.</i>

47
00:09:53,350 --> 00:09:56,020
<i>Hey, come on!
What are you guys waiting for?</i>

48
00:09:56,103 --> 00:09:59,940
We'll have you out of there
as soon as possible.

49
00:10:00,024 --> 00:10:02,108
Am I lying?

50
00:10:02,191 --> 00:10:07,655
How come they sent cops here?
Shouldn't they send repair guys?

51
00:10:15,079 --> 00:10:17,582
What do you think?

52
00:10:18,541 --> 00:10:22,796
- You're the expert. I just work here.
- Looks pretty solid.

53
00:10:22,880 --> 00:10:26,717
- Anyone we know?
- I don't recognise the work, but he's a pro.

54
00:10:28,052 --> 00:10:31,138
- He's cutting it close.
- I don't like it.

55
00:10:31,221 --> 00:10:34,141
Well, what's to like?
Mac said we hold, so we hold.

56
00:10:44,152 --> 00:10:48,031
All right, pop quiz.
The airport. Gunman with one hostage.

57
00:10:48,114 --> 00:10:51,409
He's using her for cover.
He's almost to a plane.

58
00:10:51,493 --> 00:10:54,120
You're 100 feet away.

59
00:10:59,376 --> 00:11:01,461
Jack.

60
00:11:02,504 --> 00:11:04,965
Shoot the hostage.

61
00:11:05,048 --> 00:11:07,884
- What?
- Take her out of the equation.

62
00:11:07,968 --> 00:11:12,097
Go for the good wound and he can't
get to the plane with her. Clear shot.

63
00:11:12,180 --> 00:11:15,934
You're deeply nuts, you know that?
"Shoot the hostage."

64
00:11:19,980 --> 00:11:23,316
Harry, this is wrong.
He's gonna blow it anyway.

65
00:11:24,401 --> 00:11:27,696
- Why?
- I don't know. Gut feeling.

66
00:11:28,238 --> 00:11:30,991
Right now Mac outranks your gut, so we sit.

67
00:11:31,992 --> 00:11:34,911
This is taking way too long.

68
00:11:35,578 --> 00:11:37,914
How much d'you think that elevator weighs?

69
00:11:37,998 --> 00:11:40,083
Jack, come on.

70
00:11:42,085 --> 00:11:46,006
Maybe we can do something
about those hostages.

71
00:11:46,089 --> 00:11:48,590
<i>We're not gonna shoot 'em, right?</i>

72
00:11:49,883 --> 00:11:53,012
<i>Hey, where you going?
What's going on?</i>

73
00:11:54,596 --> 00:11:58,434
<i>Don't go! Don't leave us here!</i>

74
00:12:13,198 --> 00:12:16,118
No, we just take them out of the equation.

75
00:12:48,901 --> 00:12:52,112
- Are you sure it'll hold?
- It'll hold.

76
00:12:53,364 --> 00:12:55,449
Six minutes.

77
00:12:55,532 --> 00:12:58,952
I can't get any more time. He's not talking!

78
00:12:59,036 --> 00:13:01,288
I need the goddamn money now.

79
00:13:11,423 --> 00:13:14,761
Tell me again, Harry. Why did I take this job?

80
00:13:14,844 --> 00:13:19,057
Oh, come on. 30 more years of this, you get
a tiny pension and a cheap gold watch.

81
00:13:19,140 --> 00:13:20,850
Cool.

82
00:13:20,934 --> 00:13:22,435
Ho!

83
00:13:53,382 --> 00:13:56,427
- God, it's hot in here.
- There's no air.

84
00:13:56,510 --> 00:13:59,513
- Can't they just pry the doors open?
- I can't breathe.

85
00:14:04,727 --> 00:14:07,229
Don't fuck with Daddy.

86
00:14:41,056 --> 00:14:43,475
Usually they fall down now.

87
00:14:52,442 --> 00:14:55,362
He's early. The son of a bitch is early!

88
00:15:14,589 --> 00:15:17,091
Mac, we need more help up here now!

89
00:15:17,758 --> 00:15:21,220
Oh, please! I don't wanna die!

90
00:15:21,303 --> 00:15:22,638
Please save us!

91
00:15:28,727 --> 00:15:31,814
<i>Open the door!
Open the door, please!</i>

92
00:15:35,067 --> 00:15:39,113
<i>- Please help me!
- We'll get you out!</i>

93
00:15:39,738 --> 00:15:44,243
- Give me your hands! It's OK.
- Pull me through.

94
00:15:52,751 --> 00:15:55,005
<i>Watch your head. Watch your head.</i>

95
00:15:55,088 --> 00:15:58,008
<i>- OK, I've got you.
- Take it easy.</i>

96
00:15:58,091 --> 00:16:00,844
- You're fine. You're fine.
- Thank you.

97
00:16:00,927 --> 00:16:02,721
- Take her.
- Who's next?

98
00:16:05,932 --> 00:16:07,017
Thank you.

99
00:16:08,435 --> 00:16:10,770
We've got you, ma'am.

100
00:16:16,443 --> 00:16:19,696
- What the hell is all this?
- Help us! Hurry!

101
00:16:22,907 --> 00:16:25,910
Hurry, hurry! Let's go! Go! Go!

102
00:16:26,286 --> 00:16:27,704
Come on. Come on.

103
00:16:32,626 --> 00:16:35,253
Oh, my God! Oh, my God!

104
00:16:35,337 --> 00:16:38,673
- Help me out! Please, help me out.
- Watch your head.

105
00:16:39,799 --> 00:16:41,426
- Come on, lady!
- No.

106
00:16:41,509 --> 00:16:44,220
Come on, lady! Come on! Grab my hand!

107
00:16:49,809 --> 00:16:53,021
- Come on! Let's go! It's going to fall!
- No!

108
00:16:53,104 --> 00:16:54,356
No, I can't!

109
00:16:54,439 --> 00:16:57,901
Just take one step, reach out
and take my hand.

110
00:16:57,984 --> 00:17:00,737
Come on! Come on!

111
00:17:03,822 --> 00:17:07,993
- Oh, God! Don't let go of me!
- You're OK.

112
00:17:24,343 --> 00:17:26,428
My shoe!

113
00:17:28,263 --> 00:17:29,848
Was it good for you?

114
00:17:29,932 --> 00:17:32,977
It was great for me.
How was it for you, honey?

115
00:17:33,060 --> 00:17:36,188
- Elevator dropped.
- Good. That's good to know.

116
00:17:42,361 --> 00:17:45,072
- Is your watch slow?
- No. He jumped the gun.

117
00:17:45,155 --> 00:17:48,701
- We had three minutes left.
- Why does he do that?

118
00:17:48,784 --> 00:17:50,619
He's losing his $3 million.

119
00:17:50,703 --> 00:17:53,539
Maybe he couldn't hold his wad long enough.

120
00:17:53,622 --> 00:17:58,043
It's a common problem among
middle-aged men. So I'm told.

121
00:18:03,716 --> 00:18:08,012
- He's here.
- He could've blown that thing from Pacoima.

122
00:18:08,095 --> 00:18:13,183
No. He knew we were up to something.
He's close by.

123
00:18:13,267 --> 00:18:18,480
He's not gonna corner himself in a building
we evacuated anyway. Come on.

124
00:18:23,777 --> 00:18:28,782
He'd... he'd wanna be here,
but he'd wanna stay mobile, right?

125
00:18:32,453 --> 00:18:34,288
The elevators.

126
00:18:34,372 --> 00:18:37,709
Passenger cars were stopped.
They checked 'em out.

127
00:18:37,792 --> 00:18:40,253
What about the freight elevators?

128
00:19:04,110 --> 00:19:07,656
- Will the mystery guest please sign in?
- What?

129
00:19:09,824 --> 00:19:11,785
Jack!

130
00:19:11,868 --> 00:19:13,953
Damn it.

131
00:19:54,744 --> 00:19:56,454
<i>Get to the side!</i>

132
00:20:12,762 --> 00:20:14,848
<i>Shit! Shit! Shit!</i>

133
00:20:17,058 --> 00:20:19,269
Up! Get your ass up!

134
00:21:02,686 --> 00:21:07,524
I don't suppose anybody'll give me
three million just for you.

135
00:21:12,696 --> 00:21:14,324
Hold it!

136
00:21:15,992 --> 00:21:20,538
Pop quiz, hotshot.
Terrorist holding a police hostage.

137
00:21:20,622 --> 00:21:25,961
Got enough dynamite strapped to his chest to
blow a building in half. Now what do you do?

138
00:21:26,044 --> 00:21:29,130
There's gonna be 50 cops
waiting for you in the basement.

139
00:21:29,214 --> 00:21:31,424
Standard flanking deployment, right?

140
00:21:31,508 --> 00:21:38,640
Maybe we'll get off on the third floor, huh?
At least that's what they'll think.

141
00:21:38,723 --> 00:21:42,894
I want location on those goddamn shots!
Briggs! Where's Jack and Harry?

142
00:21:42,978 --> 00:21:46,481
Lieutenant, we've got movement
on the freight elevator.

143
00:21:53,613 --> 00:21:55,407
It's on three. Let's move!

144
00:21:58,284 --> 00:22:03,123
End of the line. This day has been
real disappointing, I don't mind saying.

145
00:22:03,206 --> 00:22:05,083
Because you didn't kill everyone?

146
00:22:05,166 --> 00:22:09,087
There will come a time, boy,
when you'll wish you'd never met me.

147
00:22:09,170 --> 00:22:11,214
Mister, I'm already there.

148
00:22:11,298 --> 00:22:17,594
I'm in charge here. I drop this stick
and they pick your friend up with a sponge.

149
00:22:18,262 --> 00:22:22,224
- Are you ready to die, friend?
- Fuck you.

150
00:22:22,308 --> 00:22:26,729
In 200 years, we've come from "I regret
but I have one life to give for my country"

151
00:22:26,812 --> 00:22:27,938
to "fuck you"?

152
00:22:28,022 --> 00:22:31,191
- Go ahead. Drop the stick. Do it.
- Shut up, Harry.

153
00:22:31,275 --> 00:22:34,486
We've got all the balls
in the world right here, man.

154
00:22:34,570 --> 00:22:36,697
Give it up. You got nowhere to go!

155
00:22:37,531 --> 00:22:39,366
Shoot the hostage.

156
00:22:42,494 --> 00:22:43,829
Say goodbye, Harry.

157
00:22:49,209 --> 00:22:50,461
You fuck!

158
00:22:53,213 --> 00:22:54,131
Freeze!

159
00:22:56,008 --> 00:22:57,384
Freeze!

160
00:22:57,468 --> 00:23:00,429
Give it up! You're out of options!

161
00:23:23,745 --> 00:23:28,458
Through dedication and bravery,
these next two officers effected the rescue

162
00:23:28,541 --> 00:23:31,544
of 13 citizens of this city.

163
00:23:31,628 --> 00:23:36,341
And, thanks to them, the only life taken
by the terrorist's bomb was his own.

164
00:23:36,424 --> 00:23:38,843
You shot me. I can't believe it.

165
00:23:38,927 --> 00:23:42,097
They're giving you a medal
for shooting me, you little prick.

166
00:23:42,180 --> 00:23:45,642
Harry, you told me to.

167
00:23:45,725 --> 00:23:48,228
...the Los Angeles Police Department.

168
00:23:50,063 --> 00:23:52,148
Officer Harry Temple.

169
00:24:07,247 --> 00:24:08,748
<i>Officer Jack Traven.</i>

170
00:24:26,224 --> 00:24:28,852
Way to go, Jack. Way to go.

171
00:24:29,644 --> 00:24:31,938
- There we go.
- Harry, my man.

172
00:24:32,022 --> 00:24:36,067
Beautiful. A toast to me.
Make me feel good about myself.

173
00:24:36,151 --> 00:24:38,903
Hey, Sandy! Here we go!

174
00:24:38,987 --> 00:24:41,156
OK, so how we doing? Whoa, whoa.

175
00:24:41,239 --> 00:24:44,284
Shit. I need a bib!

176
00:24:46,119 --> 00:24:49,456
- Here we go. All right.
- You can't take me anywhere.

177
00:24:50,290 --> 00:24:52,834
And here is to Harry,

178
00:24:53,627 --> 00:24:55,962
for his quick thinking,

179
00:24:56,755 --> 00:25:01,176
for his grace under pressure
and for his brave and selfless act.

180
00:25:01,259 --> 00:25:03,345
<i>Hear! Hear!</i>

181
00:25:04,763 --> 00:25:09,267
And to Jack, for shooting Harry.

182
00:25:09,351 --> 00:25:12,687
Something we've all wanted to do
for a very long time.

183
00:25:12,771 --> 00:25:15,357
Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey!

184
00:25:15,440 --> 00:25:17,484
OK, no, no. Here it is.

185
00:25:17,567 --> 00:25:22,197
Here's to you guys for doing yourjob
and for not getting dead.

186
00:25:22,781 --> 00:25:25,075
<i>Mazel tov.</i>

187
00:25:34,417 --> 00:25:36,878
We are the two luckiest guys in the world.

188
00:25:36,962 --> 00:25:39,923
We got the bad guy
and we didn't lose any civilians.

189
00:25:40,006 --> 00:25:42,258
- We're good.
- No. You were lucky.

190
00:25:42,342 --> 00:25:46,136
No, we were lucky. You'd better understand it.

191
00:25:46,220 --> 00:25:48,889
We were dealing with a total psycho.

192
00:25:48,973 --> 00:25:52,101
This guy could've blown us up at any time.

193
00:25:52,977 --> 00:25:55,479
And I got a bullet in me.

194
00:25:55,980 --> 00:26:00,150
Six inches off the mark,
and they're giving the medal to my wife.

195
00:26:00,234 --> 00:26:03,570
Harry, come on, man.
I mean, we won. We got him.

196
00:26:03,654 --> 00:26:06,573
Do you listen? Do you ever?

197
00:26:06,657 --> 00:26:11,870
Because I am not gonna be around
to back you up, so you better start thinking.

198
00:26:13,163 --> 00:26:16,917
Guts'll get you so far,
and then they'll get you killed.

199
00:26:20,296 --> 00:26:23,257
Luck runs out sooner or later. Right, Chief?

200
00:26:23,340 --> 00:26:24,925
That's right.

201
00:26:26,802 --> 00:26:27,594
Ho!

202
00:26:27,678 --> 00:26:32,308
I'm all right. I'm all right.
I'm gonna go home, have some sex.

203
00:26:34,853 --> 00:26:40,233
- Harry, you're gonna go home and puke.
- Yeah, well, that'll be fun, too.

204
00:26:40,317 --> 00:26:42,694
Come on, you gimp.

205
00:27:04,633 --> 00:27:08,678
- Hey, Jack, saw you on TV. Congratulations.
- Thanks, Bob.

206
00:27:08,762 --> 00:27:11,139
- You looked fat.
- Take it easy on him, Bob.

207
00:27:11,222 --> 00:27:14,517
- The boy was up late last night partying.
- Wild party, huh?

208
00:27:14,601 --> 00:27:18,938
I don't remember that well.
Couldn't have been too great. Woke up alone.

209
00:27:19,022 --> 00:27:24,111
Yeah? The last time I partied like that,
I woke up married, huh, Vinnie?

210
00:27:24,945 --> 00:27:27,156
Hey, Jack, you forgot your muffins.

211
00:27:27,239 --> 00:27:30,450
- Have a good one, Bob.
- Thanks, Jack. Take care.

212
00:27:30,533 --> 00:27:32,202
Thanks.

213
00:27:44,172 --> 00:27:46,257
See you tomorrow.

214
00:29:03,126 --> 00:29:05,086
What do you think, Jack?

215
00:29:05,170 --> 00:29:10,133
You think if you pick up all the bus driver's
teeth, they'll give you another medal?

216
00:29:10,216 --> 00:29:11,217
Jesus!

217
00:29:11,301 --> 00:29:13,887
You think I wouldn't have been prepared?

218
00:29:13,971 --> 00:29:19,726
Two years I spent setting up that elevatorjob.
Two years I invested myself in it.

219
00:29:20,560 --> 00:29:23,688
<i>You couldn't understand
the kind of commitment that I have.</i>

220
00:29:23,772 --> 00:29:27,025
You ruined a man's life's work
and you think you can walk away?

221
00:29:27,108 --> 00:29:32,238
You got blinders on to the world,
but I got your attention now, didn't I, Jack?

222
00:29:32,322 --> 00:29:37,077
<i>- Why didn't you just come after me?
- This is about me. This is about my money.</i>

223
00:29:37,160 --> 00:29:41,122
This is about money due me,
which I will collect.

224
00:29:41,206 --> 00:29:43,416
$3.7 million.

225
00:29:43,917 --> 00:29:48,296
<i>It's my nest egg, Jack.
At my age, you gotta think ahead.</i>

226
00:29:48,380 --> 00:29:51,007
<i>- When I find you...
- Pop quiz, hotshot.</i>

227
00:29:51,091 --> 00:29:53,885
There's a bomb on a bus.

228
00:29:53,969 --> 00:29:58,181
Once the bus goes 50 miles an hour,
the bomb is armed.

229
00:29:58,264 --> 00:30:02,769
If it drops below 50, it blows up.

230
00:30:02,852 --> 00:30:05,689
What do you do? What do you do?

231
00:30:06,773 --> 00:30:11,528
<i>- I'd wanna know what bus it was.
- You think I'm gonna tell you that?</i>

232
00:30:11,611 --> 00:30:13,863
<i>- Yes.
- Very good.</i>

233
00:30:13,947 --> 00:30:17,367
<i>There are rules, Jack,
and I want you to get this right.</i>

234
00:30:17,450 --> 00:30:19,911
