Oh, jeez. No! No! No!

472
00:51:10,955 --> 00:51:14,750
- Why aren't they at school?
- Mac, we're boned.

473
00:51:14,834 --> 00:51:16,669
I'll get you out, Jack.

474
00:51:26,262 --> 00:51:29,307
All right, listen.
You got an entrance coming up, Jack.

475
00:51:29,390 --> 00:51:32,184
It's gonna be a real ugly turn, though.

476
00:51:32,268 --> 00:51:34,395
- How ugly?
- What's ugly?

477
00:51:34,895 --> 00:51:38,399
We got a hard right coming up
at the construction site.

478
00:51:39,108 --> 00:51:41,944
- This should be it.
- That is a dead end.

479
00:51:42,028 --> 00:51:46,449
- I can't make that turn.
- You can make it. Keep left. Make it wide.

480
00:51:46,532 --> 00:51:49,827
Oh, God. We're gonna tip over.
We're gonna tip over.

481
00:51:49,910 --> 00:51:53,831
You're right. We're gonna tip over.
Everyone on this side of the bus now!

482
00:51:53,914 --> 00:51:56,751
On this side of the bus!
As far as you can, please.

483
00:51:56,834 --> 00:51:58,918
Hold on!

484
00:51:59,002 --> 00:52:04,299
Over here. Over here. As far as you can! Now!
Mac, you better clear this site out.

485
00:52:11,640 --> 00:52:13,892
- Everybody hold on!
- This side of the bus!

486
00:52:13,975 --> 00:52:16,144
Hold on!

487
00:52:17,771 --> 00:52:21,900
Hold on! Oh, God! Here we go! Here we go!

488
00:52:25,028 --> 00:52:26,613
Here we go!

489
00:52:39,584 --> 00:52:41,503
Whoo!

490
00:52:41,586 --> 00:52:44,464
Oh, my God! Oh, God! Is everybody all right?

491
00:52:44,547 --> 00:52:46,800
- Yes!
- Oh, my God.

492
00:52:46,883 --> 00:52:49,552
Take me to that interchange at the 105.

493
00:53:00,106 --> 00:53:04,318
Oh, my God. We might've died. I can't think.

494
00:53:04,402 --> 00:53:08,114
It's OK. If you need to,
you go right ahead and vomit.

495
00:53:26,466 --> 00:53:30,679
Frank, get rid of that scaffolding
and replace it with webbing.

496
00:53:30,762 --> 00:53:34,766
Norwood, I want aerial units up ahead.
No obstructions in the freeway.

497
00:53:34,850 --> 00:53:38,395
We have a window here.
I wanna make sure it stays open.

498
00:53:59,498 --> 00:54:00,750
Shoot.

499
00:54:01,959 --> 00:54:05,630
Could you do me a favour
and hold the wheel for me for a second?

500
00:54:05,713 --> 00:54:08,132
Hold the wheel? Thank you.

501
00:54:08,215 --> 00:54:14,347
Ma'am, you did very well. Actually, you were
incredible. I've never seen driving like that.

502
00:54:14,430 --> 00:54:16,140
- Annie.
- What?

503
00:54:16,223 --> 00:54:18,100
It's my name. Annie.

504
00:54:18,684 --> 00:54:21,854
- Annie.
- As opposed to "ma'am".

505
00:54:21,937 --> 00:54:23,481
OK.

506
00:54:26,984 --> 00:54:30,446
So, why is all this happening?

507
00:54:30,529 --> 00:54:35,201
I mean, what did we do?
Bomb the guy's country or something?

508
00:54:35,284 --> 00:54:37,995
No. It's just a guy who wants money.

509
00:54:39,413 --> 00:54:42,792
I don't buy that.
It's not a very good way to make money.

510
00:54:44,085 --> 00:54:47,630
So, um... what is this guy's deal?

511
00:54:49,256 --> 00:54:52,176
A while back,
he held some people for ransom.

512
00:54:52,259 --> 00:54:55,471
It went sour,
and now he's a little pissed at me.

513
00:54:55,554 --> 00:54:59,684
- What does that have to do with us?
- Nothing. It's a game.

514
00:54:59,767 --> 00:55:03,312
If he gets the money, he wins.
If the bus blows up, he wins.

515
00:55:03,396 --> 00:55:06,065
- What if you win?
- Tomorrow we'll play another one.

516
00:55:06,148 --> 00:55:09,235
But I'm not available
to drive tomorrow. Busy.

517
00:55:13,406 --> 00:55:15,825
We got no match for that description.

518
00:55:15,908 --> 00:55:18,577
No one's lost a thumb
for at least the last 10 years.

519
00:55:18,661 --> 00:55:21,998
- He could be from anywhere.
- I can't access all that.

520
00:55:22,081 --> 00:55:25,293
Forget the files.
Start going through the pension fund.

521
00:55:25,376 --> 00:55:29,212
This guy's drawing disability. He may not
be LAPD, but he's living here now.

522
00:55:29,296 --> 00:55:32,590
I want pictures! I've seen this asshole.

523
00:55:46,855 --> 00:55:51,234
- Hey! Let's get these passengers off the bus!
- We can't do it, sir!

524
00:55:51,318 --> 00:55:55,239
There's no time for any stunts.
We gotta get these people out of harm's way.

525
00:55:55,323 --> 00:55:58,701
I got orders. We move these people, he'll see.

526
00:56:01,245 --> 00:56:03,623
Remember: Crazy, not stupid.

527
00:56:03,706 --> 00:56:08,127
Harry's trying to find out who this guy is.
We think maybe he's a cop.

528
00:56:08,210 --> 00:56:10,880
Lieutenant, it's him.

529
00:56:10,963 --> 00:56:14,383
- He wants to talk to Jack.
- He's on the line for you.

530
00:56:14,467 --> 00:56:18,387
- OK, give him the number.
- Give him the number.

531
00:56:21,057 --> 00:56:23,476
- How's he doing?
- The bleeding is less, but...

532
00:56:23,559 --> 00:56:27,188
- Are they going to help us?
- Sure they are. They're the police.

533
00:56:27,271 --> 00:56:32,068
Hey, your taxes are paying their salary.
If we die, they gotta take a pay cut.

534
00:56:34,904 --> 00:56:36,489
I mean, you know.

535
00:56:40,201 --> 00:56:41,035
Yeah.

536
00:56:41,118 --> 00:56:46,916
I think we have trust, but it looks on TV
like you're trying to get those passengers off.

537
00:56:46,999 --> 00:56:50,419
<i>- Look, you've gotta let me have one.
- We went over the rules.</i>

538
00:56:50,503 --> 00:56:54,465
As an act of faith. We have
an injured man here. The driver's been shot.

539
00:56:54,548 --> 00:56:57,259
Tell me you haven't
been shooting the passengers.

540
00:56:57,343 --> 00:57:02,306
I thought it was customary
for a police officer to shoot the bad guys.

541
00:57:02,390 --> 00:57:06,227
- This man has no time.
- No one gets off.

542
00:57:06,310 --> 00:57:11,565
It'll grease the wheels with the money men.
There's still gonna be plenty of us to kill.

543
00:57:12,608 --> 00:57:15,736
OK, son, you can try and unload the driver.

544
00:57:15,820 --> 00:57:20,157
You tell that wildcat behind the wheel
not to slow down, though,

545
00:57:20,241 --> 00:57:24,829
or he won't even get a chance
to bleed to death. And, Jack, don't slip.

546
00:57:26,289 --> 00:57:30,626
- He's letting us unload the driver.
- Norwood! Get us closer!

547
00:57:32,003 --> 00:57:34,297
- We're gonna get the driver off.
- Just him?

548
00:57:34,380 --> 00:57:36,632
- For now. Gigantor.
- Ortiz.

549
00:57:36,716 --> 00:57:40,720
Ortiz, we're gonna need your help.
I need you to pass him to me.

550
00:57:40,803 --> 00:57:43,180
Keep him straight, or the wound'll tear.

551
00:57:43,264 --> 00:57:47,018
- What about the rest of us?
- Hey, hey, hey! Lady!

552
00:57:48,769 --> 00:57:50,855
<i>I can't stay!</i>

553
00:57:52,064 --> 00:57:55,026
- How are you feeling?
- Like I've been shot.

554
00:57:55,109 --> 00:57:57,194
- Take care, Sam.
- OK, Annie.

555
00:57:58,154 --> 00:58:00,740
Drive straight!

556
00:58:03,701 --> 00:58:07,830
- Get as close as you can, OK?
- All right.

557
00:58:07,913 --> 00:58:11,459
Closer. A little closer, Annie.

558
00:58:13,169 --> 00:58:15,254
- Annie, a little closer.
- OK.

559
00:58:17,465 --> 00:58:19,967
<i>OK, how's this?</i>

560
00:58:21,594 --> 00:58:23,804
Sorry. Sorry.

561
00:58:23,888 --> 00:58:27,433
OK, Annie. No problem.
Let's try it one more time.

562
00:58:28,517 --> 00:58:30,061
A little more!

563
00:58:30,144 --> 00:58:33,273
OK! OK! Right there! Steady! Hold it steady!

564
00:58:34,566 --> 00:58:37,110
You got him? You got him?

565
00:58:43,951 --> 00:58:46,411
I'm all right. Thanks.

566
00:58:46,495 --> 00:58:48,997
- Oh, my God.
- Yes!

567
00:58:58,631 --> 00:59:00,716
<i>He's gonna be OK.</i>

568
00:59:03,552 --> 00:59:05,846
Come on! Come on, lady. Give me your hand.

569
00:59:05,930 --> 00:59:08,683
- I have to, Annie.
- No, Helen!

570
00:59:08,766 --> 00:59:10,977
- No, Helen, no!
- Come on!

571
00:59:11,060 --> 00:59:12,144
Helen, no! No!

572
00:59:12,228 --> 00:59:17,692
<i>I'm here at the 105 Freeway, where the police
have successfully led the runaway bus...</i>

573
00:59:20,403 --> 00:59:21,862
No, Helen!

574
00:59:37,295 --> 00:59:40,631
Goddamn it, Mac!
Get those fucking choppers outta here!

575
00:59:40,715 --> 00:59:44,010
<i>... was driving the bus.
Well, I couldn't tell how old...</i>

576
00:59:44,093 --> 00:59:46,971
<i>An explosion. Some kind of an explosion.</i>

577
00:59:47,054 --> 00:59:50,141
<i>The bus hasn't exploded, but... Oh, my God.</i>

578
00:59:50,224 --> 00:59:54,645
<i>A woman caught in the blast fell. She was
pulled under the wheels. This is terrible.</i>

579
00:59:54,729 --> 00:59:58,983
Interactive TV, Jack. Wave of the future, huh?

580
01:00:20,838 --> 01:00:22,923
I can't be here.

581
01:00:24,467 --> 01:00:26,469
I can't, you know...

582
01:00:27,136 --> 01:00:29,597
This is the wrong bus.

583
01:00:29,680 --> 01:00:31,766
I mean, for me to...

584
01:00:33,559 --> 01:00:35,561
I can't die here.

585
01:00:35,645 --> 01:00:37,730
Hey, shut up, man.

586
01:00:38,939 --> 01:00:41,317
- I got a wife.
- Oh, you do?

587
01:00:41,400 --> 01:00:45,987
Hey! So if you have a wife and I don't,
does that mean I'm expendable?

588
01:00:46,071 --> 01:00:48,365
What are you talking about, man?

589
01:00:48,448 --> 01:00:50,659
The guy's just talking crazy.

590
01:00:50,742 --> 01:00:53,745
He gets on my nerves.
He gets on everybody's nerves.

591
01:00:53,828 --> 01:00:59,376
- I think I have the right to be a little upset.
- What are you staring at, anyway?

592
01:00:59,459 --> 01:01:02,337
Why don't you let us all die in peace,
if it has to happen?

593
01:01:02,420 --> 01:01:07,300
Oh, so you're a really tough guy, huh?
Why don't we just step outside?

594
01:01:07,384 --> 01:01:09,469
Hey!

595
01:01:23,484 --> 01:01:25,987
How are you doing? You all right?

596
01:01:26,862 --> 01:01:28,949
What can I do?

597
01:01:30,534 --> 01:01:33,078
When that bomb went off...

598
01:01:33,161 --> 01:01:35,080
I know.

599
01:01:35,163 --> 01:01:40,043
I thought that was it.
I thought that was the bomb, and I was dead.

600
01:01:40,127 --> 01:01:44,464
And then when I saw her body fall
under the bus, it was like...

601
01:01:44,548 --> 01:01:47,050
You were glad you were still alive.

602
01:01:49,136 --> 01:01:51,888
- I'm so sorry.
- Don't be.

603
01:01:51,972 --> 01:01:54,474
You should be glad. We all are.

604
01:01:56,518 --> 01:01:59,688
- It doesn't mean you don't care.
- I know, but she was so scared.

605
01:01:59,771 --> 01:02:02,983
She was a nice lady
who didn't deserve to get killed,

606
01:02:03,066 --> 01:02:06,153
but if she'd gotten off,
it would have killed us all.

607
01:02:06,236 --> 01:02:10,699
He's the asshole, Annie. The guy
who put us here. Remember that, OK?

608
01:02:10,782 --> 01:02:13,577
Big asshole.

609
01:02:14,328 --> 01:02:16,413
OK.

610
01:02:18,624 --> 01:02:20,792
Are you sure?

611
01:02:20,876 --> 01:02:22,961
Well, how far?

612
01:02:25,839 --> 01:02:28,049
Sir, we have a serious problem.

613
01:02:29,467 --> 01:02:30,593
What?

614
01:02:30,676 --> 01:02:34,764
- This freeway isn't finished.
- What are you talking about?

615
01:02:34,847 --> 01:02:40,227
The aerial unit caught it. About three miles
ahead there's a section missing.

616
01:02:40,311 --> 01:02:42,396
A section missing?

617
01:02:47,318 --> 01:02:51,322
But it's on the map.
It's finished on the goddamn map!

618
01:02:51,405 --> 01:02:53,491
I guess they fell behind.

619
01:02:54,992 --> 01:02:58,537
Fuck! You're fired. Everybody's fucking fired!

620
01:03:00,414 --> 01:03:02,208
Get me closer!

621
01:03:02,291 --> 01:03:05,169
Hey, get closer. Watch him in the mirror.

622
01:03:05,920 --> 01:03:08,005
Jack!

623
01:03:10,257 --> 01:03:13,886
- How big is the section?
- 50 feet... at least.

624
01:03:19,225 --> 01:03:22,436
There's a gap in the road up ahead. It's big.

625
01:03:23,020 --> 01:03:26,983
- You're kidding. How big?
- 50 feet.

626
01:03:27,066 --> 01:03:28,526
What?

627
01:03:28,609 --> 01:03:31,028
We gotta get these people
off the bus somehow.

628
01:03:31,112 --> 01:03:34,198
You know I can't.

629
01:03:34,282 --> 01:03:36,784
<i>What did he say? Jack?</i>

630
01:03:38,035 --> 01:03:40,538
Jack, what did he say?

631
01:03:42,123 --> 01:03:44,375
What's the matter?

632
01:03:49,422 --> 01:03:53,385
- There's a gap in the freeway.
- What?

633
01:03:53,468 --> 01:03:56,388
<i>- What do you mean?
- How big is a gap?</i>

634
01:03:56,471 --> 01:03:59,599
50 feet. A couple of miles ahead.

635
01:03:59,683 --> 01:04:01,768
<i>This is crazy.</i>

636
01:04:06,189 --> 01:04:08,692
<i>- Jeez.
- Jack.</i>

637
01:04:08,775 --> 01:04:12,570
Jack. What if I shift into neutral
and just keep the engine revving?

638
01:04:12,653 --> 01:04:16,282
- No, he'd have thought of that.
- What, then? What? What?

639
01:04:17,074 --> 01:04:19,702
What? Jack?

640
01:04:19,785 --> 01:04:21,329
- Floor it.
- What?

641
01:04:21,412 --> 01:04:24,749
Floor it. It's an interchange.
There might be an incline.

642
01:04:24,832 --> 01:04:26,584
Fine.

643
01:04:29,378 --> 01:04:33,090
Everybody hold onto your seats
or whatever you can.

644
01:04:33,174 --> 01:04:36,260
When we hit the gap, heads down.

645
01:04:36,344 --> 01:04:38,679
That's it? That's it?

646
01:04:38,763 --> 01:04:43,893
That's all we can do. Let's put these
underneath your seat, all right?

647
01:04:43,976 --> 01:04:46,479
Put your bags underneath the seat.

648
01:04:50,983 --> 01:04:54,612
- Hey, I didn't mean to shoot the guy.
- Hold on.

649
01:04:55,780 --> 01:04:58,616
Is this really gonna work?

650
01:04:58,699 --> 01:05:00,034
<i>Jack.</i>

651
01:05:02,203 --> 01:05:04,497
Yeah?

652
01:05:04,580 --> 01:05:06,666
Jack.

653
01:05:26,936 --> 01:05:30,439
<i>- Come on, come on, come on.
- Oh, God.</i>

654
01:05:30,523 --> 01:05:32,817
- Come on!
- Oh, God.

655
01:05:42,118 --> 01:05:43,286
Oh, shit.

656
01:05:56,717 --> 01:05:59,468
Everybody hold on!

657
01:06:16,360 --> 01:06:18,738
Oh, God. Jack.

658
01:06:25,036 --> 01:06:27,121
<i>Shit!</i>

659
01:06:48,560 --> 01:06:52,940
Yes! We are way out of control!

660
01:07:00,489 --> 01:07:01,740
- You OK?
- Yeah.

661
01:07:01,823 --> 01:07:03,408
- You OK?
- I'm OK.

662
01:07:03,492 --> 01:07:06,745
All right! Norwood, let's go!

663
01:07:06,828 --> 01:07:09,706
- Is everybody OK?
- Yes!

664
01:07:12,876 --> 01:07:14,878
<i>We did it!</i>

665
01:07:14,962 --> 01:07:17,172
We made it.

666
01:07:17,255 --> 01:07:19,925
You're the man. You are the man!

667
01:07:20,592 --> 01:07:22,678
Thank you. Thank you very much.

668
01:07:24,680 --> 01:07:26,223
Oh, shit.

669
01:07:26,306 --> 01:07:30,394
- I think you missed your calling.
- Yeah? What was it?

670
01:07:30,477 --> 01:07:33,188
Watch the road.
You should have been a pilot.

671
01:07:33,271 --> 01:07:34,314
Ow.

672
01:07:41,071 --> 01:07:42,321
- Get off.
- What?

673
01:07:42,405 --> 01:07:44,490
Get off this. Now. Get off this.

674
01:07:50,663 --> 01:07:52,373
In there.

675
01:07:52,456 --> 01:07:54,375
- Where? Right here?
- Yeah.

676
01:07:54,458 --> 01:07:55,876
- Right here?
- Yeah.

677
01:08:11,892 --> 01:08:15,521
- He's just entered the airport.
- There's thousands of people there.

678
01:08:15,605 --> 01:08:18,941
That's my boy Jack. He can circle
the runways and buy us some time.

679
01:08:19,025 --> 01:08:23,863
- Choppers can't fly there. It's restricted.
- He's headed for the end of the field.

680
01:08:23,946 --> 01:08:28,284
- Bravo Tango, an emergency runway.
- Let's hope it's built. Let's move!

681
01:08:41,547 --> 01:08:44,091
We're at the airport.

682
01:08:44,175 --> 01:08:46,260
Yeah? So?

683
01:08:47,303 --> 01:08:49,388
I already seen the airport.

684
01:09:10,368 --> 01:09:14,206
- Yeah?
- Very, very exciting, Jack.

685
01:09:14,289 --> 01:09:18,543
Some close calls, huh?
But you've done all right for yourself.

686
01:09:18,627 --> 01:09:21,838
- What do you want?
- I want money, Jack.

687
01:09:21,922 --> 01:09:28,094
I wish I had some loftier purpose, but
I'm afraid in the end it's just the money, Jack.

688
01:09:28,177 --> 01:09:35,351
I would like large non-sequential bills
in two clear plastic bags, unmarked.

689
01:09:35,434 --> 01:09:39,230
- Can you remember all that?
- What are you telling me for?

690
01:09:39,313 --> 01:09:42,566
Because I want you to help me
to get it before it gets too late.

691
01:09:42,650 --> 01:09:46,529
I hate negotiators, Jack. They talk to you
like they're your best friend

692
01:09:46,612 --> 01:09:48,698
and they don't even know you.

693
01:09:48,781 --> 01:09:53,202
Why are they messing with me, huh?
Do they think I'm doing this for fun?

694
01:09:53,286 --> 01:09:56,706
<i>- Aren't you?
- Oh, that's unfair, Jack.</i>

695
01:09:56,789 --> 01:10:01,211
You don't know how I feel about this.
You don't even know me.

696
01:10:01,295 --> 01:10:03,714
You want a shitload of money
you didn't earn.

697
01:10:03,797 --> 01:10:06,008
Oh, I earned it.

698
01:10:06,091 --> 01:10:08,343
I spent my life earning it.

699
01:10:08,427 --> 01:10:14,057
<i>I got a medal, too, Jack, a medal and
a pink slip and a "sorry about your hand".</i>

700
01:10:14,141 --> 01:10:17,352
- You have to let me off.
- Oh, no.

701
01:10:17,436 --> 01:10:20,314
- That's not good.
- You want me to help you?

702
01:10:20,397 --> 01:10:24,109
I need to talk to these people face to face.
They think you're bullshit.

703
01:10:24,192 --> 01:10:26,278
They don't think that.

704
01:10:26,361 --> 01:10:31,074
Look, you want the money, I don't want
anyone else to die. Let me get on the ground.

705
01:10:31,158 --> 01:10:34,244
