736
01:13:22,954 --> 01:13:23,955
Oh, Christ.

737
01:13:34,465 --> 01:13:36,592
Just keep it steady.

738
01:13:36,676 --> 01:13:39,178
Thank you for the tip, Ortiz.

739
01:13:50,690 --> 01:13:53,901
<i>This guy is nuts!</i>

740
01:13:53,985 --> 01:13:57,196
We'll try to bypass the remote current
with the battery.

741
01:13:57,280 --> 01:14:01,951
- Can you find the tripwire for the remote?
- I don't know. I got a few choices here.

742
01:14:02,034 --> 01:14:04,787
<i>- Black and red?
- And green.</i>

743
01:14:04,870 --> 01:14:09,250
OK, I'm gonna guess he's not gonna go
with standard copper for the remote.

744
01:14:09,333 --> 01:14:11,752
That'd be too weak. I'd use a fibre alloy.

745
01:14:11,836 --> 01:14:14,964
<i>Jack, I'm gonna need you to look at the wire.</i>

746
01:14:17,301 --> 01:14:18,552
Harry, it's covered.

747
01:14:18,635 --> 01:14:22,472
I know. You're gonna have to cut off
the sheath. But don't cut the wire.

748
01:14:23,056 --> 01:14:25,142
Right.

749
01:14:37,155 --> 01:14:39,240
Fuck me!

750
01:14:40,575 --> 01:14:42,659
<i>Shit!</i>

751
01:14:47,748 --> 01:14:49,082
<i>- Bull's-eye!
- Great.</i>

752
01:14:49,166 --> 01:14:52,753
