another challenge or something?

802
01:19:06,048 --> 01:19:08,967
<i>- Mac.
- Mac here. Go ahead.</i>

803
01:19:09,051 --> 01:19:11,762
Can you get a fuel truck to pace us?
We're losing gas.

804
01:19:11,845 --> 01:19:17,392
- I'll see what I can find. How much time?
- 10 minutes? It doesn't look good.

805
01:19:17,476 --> 01:19:21,563
Gotcha. Norwood, get a fuel car
out here on the double.

806
01:19:21,647 --> 01:19:24,399
Is that gonna work?

807
01:19:24,483 --> 01:19:26,985
I don't know.

808
01:19:30,155 --> 01:19:31,531
Harry, save my life.

809
01:21:04,833 --> 01:21:07,586
Harry, tell me good news, man.

810
01:21:07,669 --> 01:21:10,505
Oh, I'm sorry, Jack. He didn't make it.

811
01:21:12,924 --> 01:21:14,551
You fuck!

812
01:21:16,345 --> 01:21:20,599
It was the watch that led him
to me, wasn't it? Huh?

813
01:21:20,682 --> 01:21:25,228
It seemed a little hammy to me to build
the bomb out of my precious retirement gift,

814
01:21:25,312 --> 01:21:31,026
but, you know, I figured a sign that said
"Howard Payne" would be pushing it.

815
01:21:33,236 --> 01:21:36,406
I'm gonna rip your fucking spine out,
I swear to God.

816
01:21:36,490 --> 01:21:39,409
You're gonna do exactly as you're told.

817
01:21:39,493 --> 01:21:43,579
<i>Jack, we both know that he was the brains
of your particular operation.</i>

818
01:21:43,663 --> 01:21:46,582
You can't beat me.
You're gonna pay me every dollar.

819
01:21:46,666 --> 01:21:51,379
Otherwise, you, the wildcat
and every innocent person on that bus

820
01:21:51,462 --> 01:21:54,382
are gonna end up just like your friend.

821
01:21:55,299 --> 01:21:59,261
Are you paying attention?
Jack, are you listening to me?

822
01:22:00,721 --> 01:22:03,683
- Jack? Jack?
- Yeah.

823
01:22:03,766 --> 01:22:08,729
Good. You tell them that
the drop point is Pershing Square.

824
01:22:10,147 --> 01:22:13,192
There's a garbage can
on the northeast corner.

825
01:22:13,276 --> 01:22:15,820
You drop the bags and leave.

826
01:22:15,903 --> 01:22:18,823
<i>I don't show until all your people are gone.</i>

827
01:22:19,699 --> 01:22:27,248
It's getting on to 11am, Jack, and I think
it's gonna be a very pretty day.

828
01:22:36,967 --> 01:22:40,721
<i>Jack.</i>

829
01:22:40,804 --> 01:22:45,350
Come on. Don't give up on me, Jack!
Jack, stop it! Jack, come on!

830
01:22:45,434 --> 01:22:48,688
Stop it, OK? Don't give up
on me right now, all right?

831
01:22:51,274 --> 01:22:56,654
We're really scared and we need you
right now. I can't do this by myself. Please?

832
01:22:56,738 --> 01:22:58,823
Jack, please.

833
01:23:03,161 --> 01:23:06,247
OK? Please. All right?

834
01:23:12,253 --> 01:23:15,840
- We're gonna die.
- No, we're not. We got this far, OK?

835
01:23:38,236 --> 01:23:40,322
I'll be damned.

836
01:23:44,076 --> 01:23:47,537
Did you go to the University of Arizona?

837
01:23:47,621 --> 01:23:49,998
- Yeah? So?
- Good football team.

838
01:23:50,958 --> 01:23:53,752
Yeah, I guess so. I don't really know.

839
01:23:53,835 --> 01:23:55,671
Arizona Wildcats.

840
01:23:57,798 --> 01:24:00,258
- Right.
- He can see you.

841
01:24:00,342 --> 01:24:04,262
- What?
- He can see you.

842
01:24:04,346 --> 01:24:07,266
Just keep looking straight ahead.

843
01:24:22,948 --> 01:24:26,868
He called you a wildcat before.
Bastard's got a camera right in your face.

844
01:24:26,952 --> 01:24:30,163
He can see the whole bus.
He's been playing me from minute one.

845
01:24:30,247 --> 01:24:34,626
- Well, he can see me, but can he hear me?
- Doesn't look like it. He's just watching.

846
01:24:34,710 --> 01:24:40,048
<i>We are following the progress
of what is turning out to be a harrowing story,</i>

847
01:24:40,132 --> 01:24:43,176
<i>as a city bus,
rigged to explode if it slows down,</i>

848
01:24:43,260 --> 01:24:46,513
<i>races around literally in circles
at the Los Angeles airport.</i>

849
01:24:46,596 --> 01:24:51,476
<i>The dead are a female passenger and a driver
of another bus, both blown up by the bomber.</i>

850
01:24:51,560 --> 01:24:57,399
<i>Others in jeopardy are the passengers of the
bus, held hostage at the whim of a madman.</i>

851
01:24:59,151 --> 01:25:01,653
"The whim of a madman."

852
01:25:02,237 --> 01:25:03,697
I like that.

853
01:25:04,448 --> 01:25:07,743
There's a camera on the bus
just over my left shoulder.

854
01:25:07,826 --> 01:25:10,828
I want you to stare straight ahead.

855
01:25:10,911 --> 01:25:14,458
Don't make any big movements, OK?

856
01:25:16,001 --> 01:25:17,836
It's Jack.

857
01:25:17,919 --> 01:25:20,005
Yeah, I know about Harry.

858
01:25:22,549 --> 01:25:24,468
Is that news van still around?

859
01:25:24,885 --> 01:25:27,804
- Get those cameras to stop taping.
- Right.

860
01:25:28,930 --> 01:25:32,184
LAPD. I need this unit.
You can broadcast UHF, right?

861
01:25:32,267 --> 01:25:35,729
There's a signal going to that bus.
I want you to find it.

862
01:25:35,812 --> 01:25:38,732
<i>We're gonna have to
take you off the air.</i>

863
01:25:38,815 --> 01:25:41,068
Please, sir, stop taping.

864
01:25:41,151 --> 01:25:44,446
Come on, hurry up. Good! Tape off of that.

865
01:25:48,033 --> 01:25:51,578
Remember, no big movements.
Just look whipped.

866
01:25:51,662 --> 01:25:54,373
That ain't gonna be too hard.

867
01:26:05,759 --> 01:26:08,679
- Tape it. Good. Come on, tape it.
- It's taping!

868
01:26:18,981 --> 01:26:20,524
- Jack.
- Yeah?

869
01:26:20,607 --> 01:26:22,693
Look.

870
01:26:26,196 --> 01:26:29,283
- Mac, fuel.
- Jack, five minutes.

871
01:26:29,616 --> 01:26:32,411
Not enough time. Run the tape.
We have to unload.

872
01:26:32,494 --> 01:26:35,163
<i>- I only have a minute of tape.
- Do it now.</i>

873
01:26:35,247 --> 01:26:39,084
I want you to make a tape and loop it
so that it runs over and over, OK?

874
01:26:41,920 --> 01:26:46,717
- All right, run it. Run it!
- All right. Tape's rolling.

875
01:26:46,800 --> 01:26:52,055
<i>We still have no live picture, but reports
are that the bus continues to circle...</i>

876
01:26:53,849 --> 01:26:57,226
<i>Everyone is safe for the moment.</i>

877
01:26:57,310 --> 01:27:01,063
<i>Hard to imagine what's going
through their thoughts at this time.</i>

878
01:27:01,147 --> 01:27:03,482
<i>Certainly, a sense of community...</i>

879
01:27:21,668 --> 01:27:24,921
Rig the steering wheel and the gas pedal.

880
01:27:27,341 --> 01:27:30,052
All right, let's get 'em off.

881
01:27:30,135 --> 01:27:32,179
OK, you, you, and you.

882
01:27:33,430 --> 01:27:38,518
<i>Police have just issued a general
statement, which doesn't tell us much more...</i>

883
01:27:38,602 --> 01:27:42,064
Grab my wrist. That's it. Good.

884
01:27:42,147 --> 01:27:44,650
Come on. Look straight ahead.

885
01:28:03,628 --> 01:28:07,131
- That's good, that's good.
- Grab my wrist.

886
01:28:07,215 --> 01:28:09,467
Put your hand out. Take his hand.

887
01:28:22,021 --> 01:28:23,982
Come on, buddy. I got ya.

888
01:28:24,065 --> 01:28:26,901
<i>Give me your hand. Your hand.</i>

889
01:28:28,695 --> 01:28:31,531
<i>Grab my hand. Don't look down.</i>

890
01:28:34,367 --> 01:28:36,327
Shit!

891
01:28:36,661 --> 01:28:38,997
Jack!

892
01:28:40,872 --> 01:28:43,917
Grab my hand! Grab my hand!

893
01:28:51,842 --> 01:28:54,177
Jack! Jack, I can't hold this any more.

894
01:28:54,845 --> 01:28:56,596
Annie!

895
01:28:56,680 --> 01:28:58,015
You... hold on!

896
01:29:01,893 --> 01:29:03,979
No! No! No!

897
01:29:06,273 --> 01:29:07,399
<i>Hold it.</i>

898
01:29:14,448 --> 01:29:18,160
- Oh, God.
- Wedge down the gas pedal.

899
01:29:21,663 --> 01:29:23,749
OK, I got it.

900
01:29:34,301 --> 01:29:37,012
- You got it?
- Yeah. I got it.

901
01:29:45,812 --> 01:29:48,815
- OK, Annie, get on.
- Jack, I can't do this.

902
01:29:49,942 --> 01:29:53,362
<i>- Let's go! Let's go!
- Shit. Shit.</i>

903
01:29:55,322 --> 01:29:56,907
- Jack.
- Shit!

904
01:29:58,492 --> 01:30:00,077
Hold on.

905
01:31:25,872 --> 01:31:27,957
Shit!

906
01:31:34,380 --> 01:31:36,549
Are you all right?

907
01:31:37,550 --> 01:31:39,969
No.

908
01:31:40,053 --> 01:31:43,306
It's OK. It's OK. It's over.

909
01:31:44,015 --> 01:31:47,936
It's over. You did it. You did it.

910
01:31:52,982 --> 01:31:55,485
